System knowledge for this geographic area was developed in connection with USGS's FRAME project for Mesa Verde National Park. This effort involves scientists and managers from USGS, BLM, Mesa Verde National Park, Colorado State University, Northern Arizona University, and Prescott College in workshops from June 2004 through November 2000
PONDEROSA PINE MOUNTAIN PINE BEETLE The basis for the probability of mountain pine beetle starts with the determination of a hazard. This hazard is based on the research work documented in "Risk Rating Guide for Mountain Pine Beetle in Black Hills Ponderosa Pine" (Stevens, McCambridge, and Edminister, 1980). Further documentation is in the users guide.
